column27: Description
column79: Custom field ([CHART] Date of First Response)

column27:
Review of documentation:
Requirements, architecture, test plan
Review of design files: gerbers, schematic, BoM etc.
Review of library components
Any performance requirements that need a more detailed report are tested.
Completion of running through the Test Plan

Time spent modifying the hardware to released baseline for example to correct hardware bugs.
Includes documenting modifications

Informal quick verification of the hardware.
Aim is to prove functionality/ discover bugs in the design before sharing outside of hardware team i.e. Software/ Customer
All activities to do with creating jigs and fixtures required for testing purposes

All manufacturing activities including:
- Manufacture review of designs
- Answering of queries
- Update of designs to accommodate manufacturers
- Update of components to accommodate availability 
- Bare board manufacturing
- PCB Assembly
- PCBA Check/ Test by manufacturers
- Delivery of hardware

Generate necessary files for manufacturing package
- Gerbers
- ODB++
- Pick and Place

- Routing of all remaining traces
- Silkscreen complete
- Assembly layer complete
- DRC checks complete
- Any schematic updates

Any work involved in getting power planes, critical nets routed:
- Schematic updates e.g. pin swaps
- Layout power constraints from power budget
- Layout of power planes
- Layout of critical nets e.g. analogue, high speed, specific layout notes

Any work spent on initial placement:
- Schematic update
- Board outline
- Initial placement
- Export of CAD for mechanical integration
- Manufacturer identified and constraints determined
- Constraints added to the board

- Mechanical model

Then create 2nd draft whilst board is in for manufacture
